# 5. かつての景色を焼きつけて

Taiga: So, what do you think?
Kohane: Um, well...
Kohane: It's a place that everybody in Vivid Street talks so highly about, so I was expecting it to be more like a big concert hall...
Kohane: The distance between the stage and the floor felt no different from any other live house.
Toya: I agree. I was also expecting to see something a little more extravagant.
Toya: Your group should've had free reign in terms of choosing a venue, Taiga, so why here...?
Taiga: Because this place felt right...
Kohane: Huh?
Taiga: We wanted to perform here because we'd been singing here forever.
Kohane: Forever...? That long?
An: Oh, Granny, what's it like backstage here?
An: There were a ton of people performing that night, so I'm wondering how you got them to all fit back there.
Owner: You want to see? Come with me.
An: Awesome! Thank you so much!
An's Voice: Geez, this place is tiny...!
Akito's Voice: Were they all sardine-canned in here...?
Taiga's Voice: Yeah, it was pretty tight. Hah hah hah.
Owner's Voice: A hot mess if you ask me.
Toya: We may want to wait until Akito and Shiraishi are done taking a look.
Kohane: Hehe. Sure.
Toya: Still, this is really the stage where Ken and Taiga sang that night...
Kohane: Yeah, this is where it happened...
Kohane: (This is what An and Shinonome have been looking up to all this time.)
Kohane: (What did they see? What was it like? I mean, it feels like it had a bigger effect on An than An's singing has had on me...)
Kohane: (No...)
Kohane: (We shouldn't be putting it on a pedestal. Our goal is to surpass RAD WEEKEND.)
Kohane: Um, Ms. Owner... Would it be alright if I stood on the stage?
Toya: Azusawa?
Kohane: I... I want to see what everything is like from up there.
Kohane: This is where An's dad and Taiga stood, so I want to see things from their perspective...
Owner: I see...
Taiga: I don't see why not?
Taiga: You want to really know what RAD WEEKEND was like, right? Then, you should be standing up there and not down here.
Kohane: ...!
Taiga: How about it, Granny? Mind letting them on stage?
Owner: Fine, do whatever you like...
An: R-Really...?! Thank you very much!
Akito: This feels weird... We actually get to stand on that stage.
Toya: Pardon us.
An: Up we go!
An: You coming, Kohane?
Kohane: One sec...!
Kohane: (This is it...)
Kohane: (This is where An's dad and Taiga really stood that night...!)
An: I'm pretty sure I was standing somewhere in the middle over there.
Kohane: Oh wow...
Toya: Where were you, Akito?
Akito: I was more towards the left. Somewhere around there.
Akito: That was the first time I'd ever been to one of these events too. I wasn't used to having to wait around for so long...
Akito: But none of that mattered once everything got started.
Kohane: ...
Miku: <Kohane.>
Kohane: Huh? Yes, Miku?
Miku: <Why don't you try singing?>
Kohane: B-But...
Miku: <Don't you want to give it a try?>
Miku: <This is where it all began. This is why our SEKAI exists.>
Kohane: Right...
Kohane: (Surpassing RAD WEEKEND wasn't originally my dream. It was something An gave me...)
Kohane: (But now it's our dream.)
Kohane: (So...)
Kohane: ♪————...
Kohane: ♪————
Kohane: ♪————!!
An: Oh...
An: (She wants to know what that night was like.)
An: (She's trying to put herself in my dad and Uncle Taiga's shoes by singing.)
An: (So...)
An: ♪————!!
Kohane & An: ♪————
Akito & Toya: ♪————
Everyone: ♪————————!!
Taiga: How about them apples, Granny...?
Owner: Hah. I was planning on kicking them out if they ended up being no good...
Owner: But for now, let's keep listening.
